This paper is primarily focused on computer security (CS) and specifically on the topic of configuring security gateways to block attack packets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with networking (NI) and distributed computing (DC) as it involves communication between multiple parties over the Internet. Additionally, the paper discusses incentives and rewards for parties involved, which falls under the category of social and information networks (SI) and game theory (DS).
